SIMPLE: subcostal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subcostal
<hw>Sub*cos"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat. &
Zool.)</fld> <def>Situated below the costas, or ribs; <as>as, the
<ex>subcostal</ex> muscles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>subcostal</xex> muscles are distinct from, and
within, the <xex>intercostal</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subcostal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subcostal
<hw>Sub*cos"tal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A subcostal muscle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the principal nervures of
the wings of an insect. It is situated next beneath or behind the
costal. See <er>Nervure</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subcranial</ent>⟦br⟧
